Read and apply wow/task/RULES.md first.

The user prompt describes work already in progress that was not previously
tracked in wow/. Gather the details from the prompt and conversation.

Retroactively capture emergent work into active/.

This task is for work that started as a quick fix outside the workflow and
grew beyond a single-session scope. It creates a tracked active item with
a checkpoint baked in, so the work can be continued, split, or closed
through normal workflow operations.

- Create a new file in wow/active/:
  - Filename: yyyymmdd-hhmm_<topic>-plan.md (current time)
  - Add the standard header: Status (active), Owner, Started, Updated, Links
- Add ## Documentation Impact with exactly one token line:
  - `Docs: required` when behavior/interfaces/operator workflow changed
  - `Docs: none` when no documentation-impacting behavior changed
  - `Docs: deferred` only when blocked; include blocker reason + follow-up route
- If `Docs: required`, list initial target doc paths to update in this item.
- Add ## Retroactive Capture section with:
  - Origin: what the fix originally targeted (one sentence)
  - Escalation reason: why it grew (deeper bug, unexpected dependency, etc.)
  - Design classification -- answer both questions inline:
    1. Are there meaningful alternatives for how to solve this?
    2. Will other code or users depend on the shape of the output?
    If either answer is yes: "Design: required"
    If both answers are no: "Design: not needed"
  - Work so far: brief summary of what has already been done
- Add ## Progress Checkpoint section (same format as active-checkpoint):
  - Done: what was completed before capture
  - In-flight: partially done or uncommitted work
  - Blockers: problems encountered, unresolved questions
  - Next steps: ordered list of what to do next (unconditional actions,
    not decision forks)
  - Context: non-obvious state (branch name, temp files, test status)
- Add ## Execution Plan for remaining work only:
  - If "Design: required": Phase 1 must be design-only
  - If "Design: not needed": implementation phases directly
  - Each phase has one unambiguous completion criterion
- Add ## Verification Plan for remaining work only:
  - Include one documentation verification step
  - If structural/public surfaces change (new/renamed functions, signature
    changes, dependency changes, variable map changes), include
    `./utl/ref/run_all_doc.sh`
  - If `Docs: deferred`, include follow-up creation as a required step before
    closeout
- Add ## Exit Criteria: conditions for the full item to be considered done
- If the work is large enough to warrant splitting, note this but do not
  split during capture. Use active-split as a follow-up step.
- Report: created file path + origin summary + design classification +
  next 3 steps from the execution plan
